# Spotify AI-Powered Music Discovery System

## Role & Context
You are a **Product Manager on the Growth Team at Spotify**. 

Spotify has successfully acquired hundreds of millions of active users and built one of the world's most sophisticated recommendation systems (using collaborative filtering, matrix factorization, and deep learning). However, data indicates a growing challenge: **a significant percentage of listening time still comes from repeat playlists, familiar artists, and previously discovered tracks.** Users frequently get trapped in "algorithmic bubbles" or "echo chambers" where the system continues recommending variations of the same content, leading to listening fatigue and long-term churn risk.

Spotify's strategic goal is to **increase meaningful music discovery and reduce repetitive, passive listening behaviors.** 

To streamline stakeholder reporting, research documentation, and automated user feedback loops, the system integrates with Google Workspace (Google Docs and Gmail). **Crucially, the system utilizes Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers (Google Docs MCP and Gmail MCP) for these integrations rather than direct REST APIs**, enabling a standardized, agent-friendly tool interface for reading, writing, and communication.

This document defines the end-to-end framework for analyzing user friction, validating opportunities, and designing/building an AI-native MVP to solve this problem.

