## Part 1: AI-Powered Review Discovery Engine
Before proposing any solution, you must build an AI-powered system that analyzes user feedback at scale to understand why users get stuck in repetitive listening cycles.

### 1. Data Sources & Target URLs
The review discovery engine must ingest and process user feedback from multiple unstructured sources:
- **Google Play Store**: Scrape feedback directly from [Spotify on Google Play Store](https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.spotify.music) to capture usability complaints and ratings.
- **Product Hunt Reviews**: Analyze launch-day and community feedback from [Spotify Reviews on Product Hunt](https://www.producthunt.com/products/spotify/reviews).
- **Apple App Store**: Collect mobile app reviews from [Spotify Reviews on Apple App Store](https://apps.apple.com/us/app/spotify-music-and-podcasts/id324684580?see-all=reviews&platform=iphone).
- **Reddit & Forums**: Monitor community boards (e.g., `r/spotify`) using Reddit's API with user agent `SpotifyDiscoveryAgent/1.0` to analyze detailed user complaints and workarounds.

### 2. Analytical Objectives & Core Insights
The engine must process the unstructured text to answer key questions:
- **Why do users struggle to discover new music?** (e.g., UI clutter, lack of trust in recommendations, difficulty articulating mood).
- **What are the most common frustrations with current recommendation algorithms?** (e.g., "recommending songs I already skipped," "too repetitive," "only plays mainstream hits").
- **What listening behaviors are users trying to achieve?** (e.g., active exploration, passive background listening, mood matching, nostalgic listening).
- **What causes users to repeatedly listen to the same content?** (e.g., cognitive overload when choosing, fear of bad recommendations, convenience).
- **Which user segments experience different discovery challenges?** (e.g., casual listeners vs. audiophiles/power users).
- **What unmet needs emerge consistently across reviews?** (e.g., "temp/sandbox mode" for listening without ruining recommendations, query-based discovery, real-time mood adjustment).

> [!NOTE]
> **Source Evidence & Insights**: User reviews and forum posts consistently point to a recurring recommendation feedback loop and a critical trust gap. Industry analyses and research show that Spotify users have varied discovery goals but often need just a few “great” new tracks to feel satisfied, reinforcing that closing this trust gap is both a user experience win and a major business opportunity.

### 3. Engine Architecture (AI-Native Stack)
You can leverage tools like **LLMs (GPT-4o, Claude 3.5 Sonnet)**, **Vector Databases (ChromaDB, Pinecone)**, **Agentic Workflows (LangGraph, n8n, CrewAI)**, and **RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation)** to:
- Scraping/Ingestion -> Cleaning -> Vector Embeddings -> Topic Modeling & Clustering -> Sentiment & Intent Classification.
- **Workspace Reporting (MCP Integration)**: Instead of implementing direct REST APIs, the workflow uses the **Google Docs MCP server** to automatically generate, format, and structure the *Review Analysis & Discovery Insights Report* directly in Google Workspace. It uses the **Gmail MCP server** to automatically draft and send synthesis email updates to growth team stakeholders at `stakeholders@spotify.com`.
- **Sandbox/Offline Fallback**: In development environments or when MCP servers are offline, all output reports must be saved locally under the `data/workspace/` directory to ensure system stability.

